entities.description: The frequency count of responses, not adjusted for sample weighting.
The percentage of total responses that fall into each category.
Categories of responses to a survey question numbered from 25 to 49, including missing data.
The count and percentage of missing data from survey responses.
The total number of responses recorded.
Measures including Mean, Minimum, Maximum, and Standard Deviation based on valid cases.
The location of cases in terms of data position or identifier.
The type of variable, which in this case is numeric.
Range of missing values for the variable.
The total number of cases considered within the survey including valid and missing data.

relationships.description: Connects a response category to its unweighted frequency count.
Connects a response category to its corresponding percentage.
Indicates the count of missing data from the survey.
Indicates the total number of survey responses recorded.
Relates the analysis to the statistical measures calculated.
Indicates the location of cases in the data.
Defines the variable type used in the survey.
Specifies the range of missing values for a variable.
Indicates the total number of cases considered, including valid and missing data.
